data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** The syntax is straightforward:

```csharp
Span<nint>  signed   = stackalloc nint[5];
Span<nuint> unsigned = stackalloc nuint[5];
```

On this 64-bit system each element is 8 bytes. The only caveat is that `sizeof(nint)` requires an `unsafe` context (since the size isn't fixed at compile time), but `stackalloc` itself works fine in safe code when assigned directly to a `Span<T>`.
